erican History |volume=99 |pages=520\u2013555 |issue=2 |doi=10.1093/jahist/jas236}} historiography\n* {{Cite book |last =Collins |first =Gilbert |year =2006 |title =Guidebook to the historic sites of the War of 1812 |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=UmbQbOcdKngC&pg=PP1|publisher=Dundurn |isbn=1-55002-626-7}}\n* Hickey, Donald R. ''The War of 1812: A Forgotten Conflict'' (1989); abridged as ''The War of 1812: A Short History'' (1995)\n* Hickey, Donald R. ''Don't Give Up the Ship!: Myths of the War of 1812'' (2006)\n* {{cite journal |last=Hickey |first=Donald R |date=Sep 2013 |title=1812: The Old History and the New |journal=Reviews in American History |volume=41 |issue=3 |pages=436\u2013444 |doi=10.1353/rah.2013.0081}}\n* Hickey, Donald R. and Connie D. Clark, eds. ''The Routledge Handbook of the War of 1812'' (2015) 336 pages\n* Jensen, Richard. [http://www.americanhistoryprojects.com/downloads/JMH1812.PDF \"Military history on the electronic frontier: Wikipedia fights the War of 1812.\"] ''Journal of Military History'' 76.4 (2012): 523\u2013556\n* {{Cite book |last=Malcomson |first=Robert |title=Historical Dictionary of the War of 1812 |location=Landham, Maryland |publisher=Scarecrow}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Perkins |first=Bradford |title=Prologue to war: England and the United States, 1805\u20131812 |year=1961 |url=http://www.ucpress.edu/op.php?isbn=9780520009967 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121203215517/http://www.ucpress.edu/op.php?isbn=9780520009967 |url-status=dead |archive-date=December 3, 2012 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Randall |first=William Sterne |title=Unshackling America: How the War of 1812 Truly Ended the American Revolution |publisher=St. Martin's Press |year=2017 |isbn=978-1-2501-1184-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JgumDQAAQBAJ&vq=decatur}}\n* Sapio, Victor. ''Pennsylvania and the War of 1812'' (University Press of Kentucky, 2015).\n* Smith, Gene Allen. ''The Slaves' Gamble: Choosing Sides in the War of 1812.'' New York: Pa